I hope this email finds you well

I have receievd this email from the third party insurer:

As we previously informed you that for cash in lieu we need to refer the
shared documents to our engineers which we did. Our engineers have asked to
share the images of the third-party vehicle showing damages to the nearside
of the vehicle up close which clearly show damages & also share the
estimate used to calculate the repair costs weather than be an audatex
estimate or gt motive etc.

I will request further images from the client regarding the damages,
however is their any way you can assist with what they are requesting? I am
not entirely sure what they mean by this?

Thank you

Kind regards

*Georgia Gascoyne*

